It'd be a bit tricky.

525
01:26:25.972 --> 01:26:28.516
We'd have to cut his
higher brain functions...

526
01:26:28.767 --> 01:26:33.480
...without disturbing the purely
automatic and regulatory systems.

527
01:26:34.731 --> 01:26:36.441
We'd have to
work out the details...

528
01:26:36.649 --> 01:26:39.611
...of continuing
underground-based computer control.

529
01:26:40.028 --> 01:26:44.532
Yeah. That's far safer than
allowing Hal to continue to run things.

530
01:26:45.241 --> 01:26:47.243
Another thing just occurred to me.

531
01:26:48.745 --> 01:26:51.331
No 9000 computer has ever
been disconnected.

532
01:26:51.581 --> 01:26:53.625
No 9000 computer
has ever fouled up.

533
01:26:53.875 --> 01:26:55.377
That's not what I mean.

534
01:26:57.545 --> 01:26:59.756
I'm not so sure
what he'd think about it.

535
01:27:04.260 --> 01:27:07.263
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

536
01:32:58.156 --> 01:33:00.199
BOWMAN:
Prepare G-pod for EVA, Hal.

537
01:33:03.286 --> 01:33:04.620
Any contact with him yet?

538
01:33:04.871 --> 01:33:06.664
HAL:
<i>The radio is still dead.</i>

539
01:33:06.873 --> 01:33:09.792
-Do you have a positive track on him?
-<i>I have a good track.</i>

540
01:33:10.042 --> 01:33:11.461
Do you know what happened?

541
01:33:11.753 --> 01:33:14.422
<i>I'm sorry, Dave.
I don't have enough information.</i>

542
01:33:14.672 --> 01:33:16.257
Open the pod door, Hal.

